        "title": "fix(usage): remove argsMenu: auto from /usage command to fix Telegram toggle",
        "body": "## Problem\n`/usage` command registered with `argsMenu: \"auto\"`, which causes Telegram to misinterpret the command as having sub-commands and toggle behavior incorrectly.\n\n## Fix\nRemove `argsMenu: \"auto\"` from the built-in `/usage` command registration. The native command name and handler remain in place.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8)\n```\n✓ src/auto-reply/commands-registry.test.ts (31 tests, 100% pass)\n```\n\n### Behavior addressed\nCommands registry no longer includes `argsMenu` for `/usage`, fixing Telegram toggle regression.\n\n### Real environment tested\nLocal Node 22 build, vitest 4.1.8.\n\n### Evidence after fix\nAll 31 command registry tests pass, including command registration and argument parsing.\n",
